4 potato
1 lemon
1 sachet dukkah
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
1 bag herbs
olive oil

Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Zest lemon to get a pinch, then slice
into wedges.

Cut potatoes into bite-sized chunks. On a lined oven tray, place potatoes,
dukkah and a good squeeze of lemon juice. Drizzle with olive oil, then season
with salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly and roast for 20 minutes.

After the potato has been roasting for 20 minutes, remove from oven and
sprinkle with lemon zest. Roast until potato is tender, 5 minutes.

Transfer zesty roasted dukkah potatoes to a serving dish. Crumble with Greek
salad cheese (see ingredients). Tear over herbs. Serve with remaining lemon
wedges.